Nanopore Adaptive Sequencing of Mosquito Microbiome (Metagenome) Analysis Pipeline

This repository contains a workflow for long-read metagenomic analysis using Oxford Nanopore sequencing data. The pipeline covers basecalling, QC, assembly, taxonomic profiling, functional annotation, genome binning, and host contamination filtering.

📌 Overview
This pipeline processes raw Nanopore POD5 data into:

High-quality microbial assemblies
Taxonomic profiles (reads + contigs)
Functional gene annotations
Metagenome-assembled genomes (MAGs)
Host vs microbial separation
Adaptive sequencing target sets


⚙️ Workflow Summary
Basecalling & Demultiplexing (Dorado)
Quality Control & Filtering (NanoPlot, NanoFilt)
Read-level Taxonomy (Kaiju)
Metagenome Assembly (Flye)
Contig-level Taxonomy (Kraken2)
Functional Annotation (Prokka, eggNOG-mapper)
Read Mapping & Coverage Estimation (Bowtie2, Samtools)
Genome Binning (MetaBAT2, MaxBin2, MetaCoAG)
Bin Refinement (DAS Tool)
Bin Quality Assessment (CheckM)
Taxonomic Classification (GTDB-Tk)
Host Contamination Filtering (BLAST + NCBI nt)
Adaptive Sequencing Target Generation


📁 Directory Structure
1_pod5/                  # Raw POD5 files
2_demultiplex/          # Basecalled FASTQ files
3_nanofilt/             # Filtered reads
4_kaiju_reads/          # Read-level taxonomy
5_assembly/             # Flye assembly output
6_kraken/               # Contig taxonomy (Kraken2)
7_prokka/               # Gene annotation
8_eggnog/               # Functional annotation
9_binning/              # BAM + depth files
10_dastool/             # Refined MAGs
11_checkm/              # Genome quality stats
12_gtdbtk/              # Taxonomic classification
13_host_check/          # BLAST host filtering
14_contig_split/        # Host vs microbial contigs
15_adaptive_targets/    # Adaptive sequencing references


🧪 Software Requirements

This pipeline is designed for HPC environments and relies on module systems.

Required modules (versions depend on your system):
Dorado (Nanopore basecalling)
Flye (metagenome assembly)
Kraken2 (taxonomic classification)
Kaiju (read classification)
NanoPlot / NanoFilt (QC)
Prokka (gene annotation)
eggNOG-mapper (functional annotation)
Bowtie2 / Samtools (mapping)
MetaBAT2 / MaxBin2 / MetaCoAG (binning)
DAS Tool (bin refinement)
CheckM (quality assessment)
GTDB-Tk (taxonomy)
BLAST + NCBI edirect (host detection)
seqtk (sequence extraction)


🧬 Input Data
Nanopore POD5 sequencing files
Optional: host reference genome (mosquito_genome.fa or similar)


🚀 How to Run
Run the full pipeline:
bash pipeline.sh
sbatch pipeline.sh

Make sure to edit the configuration section:
RAW_DIR="1_pod5"
THREADS=30
KAIJU_DB="$HOME/kaijudb"
KRAKEN_DB="$HOME/standard_database"
GTDBTK_DATA_PATH="$HOME/gtdb_database"

🧠 Key Outputs
🧾 Taxonomy
Kaiju (reads)
Kraken2 (contigs)
GTDB-Tk (MAGs)

🧬 Assembly
Flye metagenome assembly (assembly.fasta)

🧫 Functional annotation
Prokka gene calls
eggNOG functional categories

🧱 Genome bins (MAGs)
MetaBAT2 bins
MaxBin2 bins
MetaCoAG bins
DAS Tool refined bins

🧪 Quality
CheckM completeness & contamination

🧍 Host filtering
BLAST-based mosquito vs microbial separation

🔬 Adaptive Sequencing Module
The pipeline generates:
Depletion targets (Host genome + host contigs)
Enrichment targets (Microbial contigs only)

These are used for ONT adaptive sequencing (e.g., read rejection/enrichment).

📊 Example Applications
Mosquito microbiome profiling
Environmental metagenomics
Host-associated microbial assembly
Adaptive sequencing design
MAG recovery and annotation

⚠️ Notes
Designed for HPC clusters (SLURM-compatible environments)
Some tools require pre-built databases (Kraken2, GTDB, Kaiju)
BLAST remote mode may be slow for large datasets
Ensure sufficient storage for intermediate BAM files


